  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Bash your<strong> lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, remove the <strong>tough outer layers</strong>, set aside the <strong>soft inner core[s]</strong> for later</p><p>Rinse your <strong>sushi rice </strong>in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong> for 30 secs, then set aside to drain fully</p><p>Add your <strong>drained rice</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with the <strong>outer lemongrass layers</strong> and 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong>, then cover tightly with<strong> tin foil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 25 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1719400282813-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1719400282813-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1719400282813-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
